		<p>I love this bread too!  To help make putting the loaf in the scalding pot, Cook&#8217;s Illustrated suggests doing the second rise in a 10-inch skillet lined with foil.  Once you are ready to move it to the dutch oven, you just lift the foil and set it gently in the hot pan.  I usually push the edges down with a wooden spoon.  Works like a charm every time!</p>

